author: @adhirajmajumder
text: select first_name,salary,department,salary from worker where salary IN (select max(salary) from worker group by department) union select first_name,salary,department,salary from worker where salary IN (select min(salary) from worker group by department);  each department highest and lowest salary,

author: @adhirajmajumder
text: select w1.salary,w1.first_name,w1.department from worker w1 where 4=(select count(distinct salary) from worker w2 where w1.worker_id<>w2.worker_id and w1.salary<=w2.salary); or   select salary,worker_id,first_name,Last_name,joining_date,department  from ( select salary,worker_id,first_name,Last_name,joining_date,department, dense_rank() over(order by salary desc) as 'rnk' from worker) as t where rnk=5;

text: For the last question.  select FIRST_NAME,WORKER_TITLE ,DEPARTMENT,salary from WORKER,title where WORKER_ID=WORKER_REF_ID  and salary in ( select max(salary) from WORKER group by DEPARTMENT); select DEPARTMENT,max(salary) from WORKER group by DEPARTMENT
